data.name: accept_language
data.description: Custom accept-language header string for the web request.

data.name: access_token
data.description: You can provide your token via querystring instead of header.

data.name: base64
data.description: Serialize response file to base64

data.name: css
data.description: Additional CSS string to be injected into the page before render.

data.name: delay
data.description: Time in milliseconds to delay capture after page load. Default: 2000 Max: 10000

data.name: element_selector
data.description: A CSS selector to be used with element rendering mode.

data.name: format
data.description: Preferred image output format. If you need a raw html string you can pass html as format Default: png Pattern: jpg | png | pdf | html

data.name: fresh
data.description: Force rendering a new screenshot disregarding the cache status. Default: false

data.name: headers
data.description: Additional headers seperated with newline Example: X-Test: header\nAccept-Type: html

data.name: height
data.description: Preferred viewport height in pixels. Default: 1024 Min: 160

data.name: html
data.description:
Raw HTML string of a page that you want to capture. Example:

Test

data.name: js
data.description: Additional JS string to be injected into the page before render.

data.name: json
data.description: Return a JSON response with the resulting image's URL instead of the image itself. Default: false

data.name: mode
data.description: Capturing mode. Please see below for details. Default: fullpage Pattern: fullpage | viewport | element

data.name: prescroll
data.description: Force scrolling the webpage before capture. Might help with dynamic loading assets.

data.name: retina
data.description: Generate retina sized screen capture (2x device pixel ratio). Default: false

data.name: thumbnail_height
data.description: Preferred thumbnail height, requires thumbnail_width to be set, unbounded if omitted. Min: 10 Max: 3000

data.name: thumbnail_width
data.description: In case you want a thumbnail image, provide a preferred width. Min: 10 Max: 3000

data.name: ttl
data.description: Time in milliseconds for the resulting image to be cached for further requests. Default: 1 day Max: 1 week

data.name: url
data.description: The URL of web page, including the protocol that you want to capture.

data.name: user_agent
data.description: Custom user-agent header string for the web request. Default: Chrome Compatible User Agent

data.name: width
data.description: Preferred viewport width in pixels. Default: 1280 Min: 320 Max: 2000
Capture screenshot from any URL or Raw HTML. POST method is also available. Please take a look https://restpack.io/screenshot/docs
data.name: /capture

description: Take pixel-perfect screenshots or thumbnails of any website. Restpack Screenshot API is an easy to use RESTful web service that can capture screenshots of live web pages and deliver the results in several formats. The service sits on a fully functional browser rendering engine with rich html / css / js capabilities.
name: v1
